\n* Somali: {{tt|so|kursi|m}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|stoł|m}}\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{tt|hsb|stólc|m}}\n* Sotho: {{tt+|st|setulo}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|silla|f}}, {{tt+|es|asiento|m}}, {{t+|es|butaca|f}}, {{t+|es|cadera|f}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|sturu}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|kiti}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|stol|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|silya}}, {{tt+|tl|upuan}}, {{tt|tl|luklukan}}\n* Tai Dam: {{tt|blt|ꪔꪰ꪿ꪉ}}\n* Tai Nüa: {{tt|tdd|ᥖᥒᥱ}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|сандали}}, {{tt+|tg|курсӣ}}, {{tt|tg|курси}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|நாற்காலி}}, {{tt+|ta|கதிரை}} {{q|Sri Lanka}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|урындык}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|కుర్చీ}}, {{tt+|te|చేరు}}, {{tt+|te|ఆసనం}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|เก้าอี้}}, {{tt+|th|ตั่ง}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{t-needed|nod}}\n*: Southern Thai: {{t-needed|sou}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|རྐུབ་ཀྱག}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt+|ti|መንበር}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|sia}}\n* Tonga (Zambia): {{t|toi|cuuna}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|koltuk}}, {{tt+|tr|iskemle}}, {{tt+|tr|sandalye}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{tt|ota|اسكمله|tr=iskemle}}, {{tt|ota|سجه|tr=sece}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|oturgyç}}, {{tt|tk|kürsi}}\n* Ugaritic: {{tt|uga|𐎋𐎈𐎉}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|стіле́ць|m}}, {{tt|uk|крі́сло|n}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|آسَنْد|m}}, {{tt|ur|کُرْسی|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|ئورۇندۇق}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|oʻrindiq}}\n* Venetan: {{tt+|vec|carega|f}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|ghế}}\n* Vilamovian: {{tt|wym|śtül|m}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|jäd}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|tcheyire|f}}, {{tt+|wa|tchereye|f}}, {{tt+|wa|sele|f}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|cadair|f}}, {{tt|cy|ystôl|f}}, {{tt+|cy|cadeiriau|f-p}}\n* Winnebago: {{tt|win|waamįnąk}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|олоппос}}, {{tt|sah|устуул}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|שטול|m}}, {{tt|yi|בענקל|n}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|eij}}, {{tt|za|daengq}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|isihlalo|c7|c8}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|chairperson}}\n\n{{trans-top|distinguished professorship}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|كُرْسِيّ مُعَلِّم|m}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|kador-gelenn}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|катедра|f}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|càtedra|f}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|leerstoel}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|chaire|f}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Lehrstuhl|m}}\n* Irish: {{t-check|ga|ollúnacht|f}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|kursi}}\n* Malayalam: {{t-check|ml|അദ്ധ്യക്ഷസ്ഥാനം}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|professorat|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|professorat}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|cátedra|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|cathair|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|eminencia|f}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|ка́федра|f}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|pirlodje|f}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|קאַטעדרע}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+check|af|stoel|m}}\n* German:\n*: Bavarian: {{t-check|bar|Stui}}, {{t-check|bar|Sessl}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t-check|grc|κᾰθέδρᾱ|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+check|he|כיסא|m|tr=kise'}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|sede}}, {{t-check|ia|cathedra}}\n* Latin: {{t-check|la|cathedra|f}}\n* Malayalam: {{t+check|ml|കസേര}}, {{t+check|ml|പീഠം}}\n* Romanian: {{t+check|ro|scaun|n}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t-check|si|පුටුඹක්}}\n* Swahili: {{t+check|sw|kiti}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|act as chairperson}} {{lb|en|transitive}} To act as [[chairperson]] at; to [[preside]] over.\n#: {{ux|en|Bob will '''chair''' tomorrow's meeting.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2000|author=David Golinkin|title=Responsa in a Moment|volume=3|chapter=Institutionalizing Parents With Alzheimer's Disease|page=38|text=Dama ben Netina, the gentile \"Mayor\" of first-century Ashkelon, was once '''chairing''' a meeting of the City Council.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2020 May 20|title=Merriman praised over handling of TSC's 'virtual' transition|journal=Rail|page=12|text=Greenwood told ''RAIL'' she was disappointed that Parliamentary rules prevented her from '''chairing''' the TSC <small>[Transport Select Committee]</small> beyond last December's General Election, [...] She added: \"I'm gutted I'm no longer able to '''chair''' the committee, I'm not going to lie. But I know it's in good hands and I'm still able to play my part as a member in the work we're doing.}}\n# {{senseid|en|carry on shoulders}} {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[carry]] in a [[seated]] [[position]] upon one's [[shoulders]], especially in [[celebration]] or [[victory]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1896|author=w:A. E. Houseman|chapter=To An Athlete Dying Young,|title=A Shropshire Lad\n|passage=The time you won your town the race<br>We '''chaired''' you through the marketplace.}}\n# {{senseid|en|give award for poetry}} {{lb|en|transitive|Wales|UK}} To [[award]] a chair to (a winning [[poet]]) at a [[Welsh]] [[eisteddfod]].\n#: {{ux|en|The poet was '''chaired''' at the national Eisteddfod.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|to act as chairperson}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Bengali: {{tt|bn|চেয়ারপারসন}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|председателствувам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|presidir}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|prezidi}}\n* Finnish: {{tt|fi|[[johtaa]] [[puhetta]]}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|présider}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Vorsitz|m}} {{tt+|de|führen}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|presiedere}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|претседава}}, {{tt|mk|води}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|présider}} {{q|Jersey}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|comandar}}, {{tt+|pt|dirigir}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|presidir}}, {{tt+|es|dirigir}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|başkanlık etmek}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{trans-top|to award a chair to}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|cadeirio}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=achir|Archi|Chira|archi-}}\n\n{{cln|en|gender-neutral terms}}\n{{C|en|Furniture|Isomer (chemistry)|People}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|fr|frm|chair}}, {{m|frm|char}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|char}}, {{m|fro|charn}} (earlier {{m|fro|carn}}), from {{inh|fr|la|carō|carnem, carō}}, from {{inh|fr|itc-pro|*karō}}, from {{der|fr|ine-pro|*ker-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*(s)ker-}}. {{dbt|fr|carne}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-chair.ogg|text=la chair}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Benoît Prieur-chair.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Saint-Maurice-de-Beynost>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DSwissK-chair.wav|a=<<Switzerland>> (<<Valais>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-chair.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-chair.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Mecanautes-chair.wav|a=France}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-chair.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-chair.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{rhyme|fr|ɛʁ|s=1}}\n* {{hmp|fr|chaire|chaires|chairs|cher|chers|chère|chères|cherres}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# [[flesh]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|fr|bien en chair\n|chair à canon\n|chair à plaisir\n|chair de poule\n|en chair et en os\n|ni chair ni poisson\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col4|fr|carnage\n|carnaire\n|carné\n|carnier\n|carnifier\n|carnivore\n|charcuterie\n|charnel\n|charnier\n|charnu\n|incarner\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ht|chè}}\n* {{desc|sv|skär|bor=1}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Gallo==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|roa-gal|verb}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|roa-gal|chaeir}}\n#: {{ux|roa-gal|Une avion san liméro qu'est '''chaite''' ste netey à Eastdown dan le Sussex|A plane without number that has '''crashed''' this night at Eastdown, Sussex}}\n\n==Manx==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|gv|mutated adjective}}\n\n# {{lenition of|gv|cair}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|gv|mutated noun|g=f}}\n\n# {{lenition of|gv|cair}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{gv-mut-cons|c|air}}\n\n==Middle French==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|frm|char}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frm|fro|char}}, {{m|fro|charn}}, from {{inh|frm|la|carnem}}, accusative singular of {{m|la|carō}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{frm-noun|f}}\n\n# [[flesh]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fr|chair}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fro|verb}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|fro|cheoir}}"}}